===2010 census===
The [[2010 United States census]] counted 273 people, 105 households, and 79 families in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|393.3|/sqmi}}. There were 108 housing units at an average density of {{convert|155.6|/sqmi}}. The racial makeup was 99.27% (271) [[White (U.S. census)|White]], 0.00% (0) [[Black (U.S. census)|Black or African American]], 0.00% (0) [[Native American (U.S. census)|Native American]], 0.37% (1) [[Asian (U.S. census)|Asian]], 0.00% (0) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.37% (1) from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]], and 0.00% (0) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. census)|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 0.73% (2) of the population.<ref name=Census2010>[http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3401900 DP-1 - Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data for Asbury CDP, New Jersey] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212134158/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3401900 |date=2020-02-12 }}, [[United States Census Bureau]]. Accessed June 3, 2013.</ref>

Of the 105 households, 31.4% had children under the age of 18; 59.0% were married couples living together; 9.5% had a female householder with no husband present and 24.8% were non-families. Of all households, 21.0% were made up of individuals and 7.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.60 and the average family size was 2.99.<ref name=Census2010/>

23.8% of the population were under the age of 18, 6.6% from 18 to 24, 22.3% from 25 to 44, 37.7% from 45 to 64, and 9.5% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43.4 years. For every 100 females, the population had 99.3 males. For every 100 females ages 18 and older there were 100.0 males.<ref name=Census2010/>

===2000 census===
